TOPOS =C3=80 L'IHES=20
Call for participation

23-27 November 2015
Institut des Hautes =C3=89tudes Scientifiques=20
https://indico.math.cnrs.fr/event/747/


* Scope *
------------

The conference aims to illustrate the fruitfulness and wide-ranging=20
impact of the theory of Grothendieck toposes, by featuring presentations =
on=20
new theoretical advances in the subject (including the theory of higher =
toposes)=20
as well as on applications of toposes in different fields such as number =
theory,=20
algebraic geometry, logic, functional analysis, topology, mathematical =
physics=20
and computer science.=20

The conference is preceded by a two-day introductory mini-course for the =

benefit of students and mathematicians who are not already familiar with =
topos theory.


* Scientific Committee *
-------------------------------

Olivia CARAMELLO
Pierre CARTIER
Alain CONNES
St=C3=A9phane DUGOWSON
Anatole KHELIF


